# TypeScript Coding Standards

## Code Style
- **Semicolons**: Always use semicolons (enforced by ESLint)
- **Quotes**: Use single quotes (enforced by ESLint and Prettier)
- **Indentation**: 2 spaces (enforced by ESLint and Prettier)
- **Line endings**: Unix style (LF)
- **Trailing commas**: ES5 style (enforced by Prettier)
- **Print width**: 80 characters max

## TypeScript Best Practices
- **Strict mode**: Always enabled in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)
- **Module resolution**: Use ES modules with bundler resolution
- **JSX**: Use React JSX transform (no need to import React in React 19)
- **Type annotations**: Prefer explicit types for function parameters and return values
- **Interfaces**: Use interfaces for object shapes and component props

## React Component Standards
- **Component naming**: Use PascalCase for components
- **Props interface**: Define props interface above component
- **Type annotations**: Use React.FC<Props> or explicit return types
- **State management**: Use React hooks (useState, useEffect, useInput from Ink)

## File Organization
- **Source files**: Place all source code in [src/](mdc:src/) directory
- **Entry points**: Use [src/index.tsx](mdc:src/index.tsx) for React app, [src/index.ts](mdc:src/index.ts) for CLI
- **Component files**: One component per file with matching filename
